{"author":{"id":"fa143ccb44437cf4ba0e7406c290e7f37ed62c10d982761b27b808b363cd753f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1661369903,"nonce":"jahA2I8/TLfJ8yx/LDW24E1esgA=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s5Qdl8l","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4750","origin":"github"},"title":"SRAtoolkit-error on newly submitted SRA files.","message":"Hi,\n\nI was recently trying to download some recently submitted SRA files (SRR21141200) from ncbi using SRAtools on galaxy and i am getting this error.\n\n fasterq-dump log\n2022-08-24T19:21:30 fasterq-dump.2.11.0 err: incorrect while parsing path within network system module - Port is '0' 2022-08-24T19:21:30 fasterq-dump.2.11.0 err: incorrect while parsing path within network system module - error with https open 'https://h\nAn error occurred with this dataset\n2022-08-24T19:21:30 fasterq-dump.2.11.0 err: incorrect while parsing path within network system module - Port is '0'\n2022-08-24T19:21:30 fasterq-dump.2.11.0 err: incorrect while parsing path within network system module - error with https open 'https://h\n\nWhen i tried to contact ncbi regarding this error. They had responded saying only the newest version of sratoolkit (3.0.0) will have full support of all new SRA files.Please check their response below and can you please let me know if you can upgrade the newest version of SRAtools on galaxy?\n\nThanks,,\nJayanthi\n\nHello,\n \nDue to backend changes, only the newest version of sratoolkit (3.0.0) will have full support of all files. Some files work because they are still stored on NCBI's servers, but a larger proportion of our offerings are being offloaded to AWS/GCP, and older versions of sratoolkit do not properly support pulling files from those sources (leading to errors).\n \nCharlie Seto[C]\nSRA Curator","files":null}]}